{"parse":{"title":"Minority languages of Austria","pageid":47538858,"revid":854207492,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;background-color:#efefef;\">Languages of Austria</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Ludmannsdorf_(Ortstafel).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Ludmannsdorf (Ortstafel).jpg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Ludmannsdorf_%28Ortstafel%29.jpg/220px-Ludmannsdorf_%28Ortstafel%29.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"165\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Ludmannsdorf_%28Ortstafel%29.jpg/330px-Ludmannsdorf_%28Ortstafel%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Ludmannsdorf_%28Ortstafel%29.jpg/440px-Ludmannsdorf_%28Ortstafel%29.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1280\" data-file-height=\"960\" /></a><div>A bilingual sign in <a href=\"/wiki/Ludmannsdorf\" title=\"Ludmannsdorf\">Ludmannsdorf</a></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/Minority_language\" title=\"Minority language\">Minority languages</a></th><td>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Croatian_language\" title=\"Croatian language\">Croatian</a><br /></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Czech_language\" title=\"Czech language\">Czech</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Hungarian_language\" title=\"Hungarian language\">Hungarian</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Romany_language\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Romany language\">Romany</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Slovak_language\" title=\"Slovak language\">Slovak</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Slovene_language\" title=\"Slovene language\">Slovene</a></li></ul>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Minority_languages\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Minority languages\">Minority languages</a> are spoken in a number of autochthonous settlements in <a href=\"/wiki/Austria\" title=\"Austria\">Austria</a>. These are: \n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Croatian_language\" title=\"Croatian language\">Croatian</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Romany_language\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Romany language\">Romany</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Burgenland\" title=\"Burgenland\">Burgenland</a>,</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Czech_language\" title=\"Czech language\">Czech</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Slovak_language\" title=\"Slovak language\">Slovak</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Vienna\" title=\"Vienna\">Vienna</a>,</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Hungarian_language\" title=\"Hungarian language\">Hungarian</a> in Burgenland and Vienna, and</li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Slovene_language\" title=\"Slovene language\">Slovene</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Carinthia\" title=\"Carinthia\">Carinthia</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Styria\" title=\"Styria\">Styria</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3R_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3R-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<p>The <a href=\"/wiki/Austrian_Federal_Constitution\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Austrian Federal Constitution\">Austrian Federal Constitution</a> calls for the respect and promotion of ethnic groups resident in Austria and a special set of rights for Austrian <a href=\"/wiki/Burgenland_Croats\" title=\"Burgenland Croats\">Croats</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Czechs_in_Austria\" title=\"Czechs in Austria\">Czechs</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Hungarians_in_Austria\" title=\"Hungarians in Austria\">Hungarians</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Romani_people_in_Austria\" title=\"Romani people in Austria\">Romani</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Slovaks_in_Austria\" title=\"Slovaks in Austria\">Slovaks</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Carinthian_Slovenes\" title=\"Carinthian Slovenes\">Slovenes</a> was established under the terms of the Ethnic Group Act (<a href=\"/wiki/German_language\" title=\"German language\">German</a>: <i><span lang=\"de\">Volksgruppengesetz</span></i>) 1976.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Federal_Ministry_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Federal_Ministry-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The rights of Croats and Slovenes are also set forth in the <a href=\"/wiki/Austrian_State_Treaty\" title=\"Austrian State Treaty\">Austrian State Treaty</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Federal_Ministry_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Federal_Ministry-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Austria signed the <a href=\"/wiki/European_Charter_for_Regional_or_Minority_Languages\" title=\"European Charter for Regional or Minority Languages\">European Charter for Regional or Minority Languages</a> on 5 November 1992 and application of the charter became effective under <a href=\"/wiki/International_law\" title=\"International law\">international law</a> on 1 October 2001.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3R_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3R-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>In the view of the representatives of the speakers of minority languages, however, the federal laws concerning regional or minority languages, as well as the application in Austria of the European Charter for Regional or Minority Languages, remain too restrictive.<sup id=\"cite_ref-COE3_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-COE3-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Minority_languages_of_Austria&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-3R-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-3R_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-3R_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.bka.gv.at/DocView.axd?CobId=45600\">\"3rd Report of the Republic of Austria-pursuant to Article 15 (1) of the European Charter for Regional or Minority Languages\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Federal_Chancellery_of_Austria\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Federal Chancellery of Austria\">Federal Chancellery of Austria</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">16 August</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=3rd+Report+of+the+Republic+of+Austria-pursuant+to+Article+15+%281%29+of+the+European+Charter+for+Regional+or+Minority+Languages&amp;rft.pub=Federal+Chancellery+of+Austria&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bka.gv.at%2FDocView.axd%3FCobId%3D45600&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMinority+languages+of+Austria\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Federal_Ministry-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Federal_Ministry_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Federal_Ministry_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.bmeia.gv.at/en/european-foreign-policy/human-rights/priorities-of-austrian-human-rights-policy/rights-of-minorities/\">\"Rights of Minorities\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/Federal_Ministry_for_Europe,_Integration_and_Foreign_Affairs\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Federal Ministry for Europe, Integration and Foreign Affairs\">Federal Ministry for Europe, Integration and Foreign Affairs</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">16 August</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Rights+of+Minorities&amp;rft.pub=Federal+Ministry+for+Europe%2C+Integration+and+Foreign+Affairs&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bmeia.gv.at%2Fen%2Feuropean-foreign-policy%2Fhuman-rights%2Fpriorities-of-austrian-human-rights-policy%2Frights-of-minorities%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMinority+languages+of+Austria\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-COE3-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-COE3_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.coe.int/t/dg4/education/minlang/Report/EvaluationReports/AustriaECRML3_en.pdf\">\"EUROPEAN CHARTER FOR REGIONAL OR MINORITY LANGUAGES-APPLICATION OF THE CHARTER IN AUSTRIA 3rd monitoring cycle\"</a> <span style=\"font-size:85%;\">(PDF)</span>. <a href=\"/wiki/Council_of_Europe\" title=\"Council of Europe\">Council of Europe</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">16 August</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=EUROPEAN+CHARTER+FOR+REGIONAL+OR+MINORITY+LANGUAGES-APPLICATION+OF+THE+CHARTER+IN+AUSTRIA+3rd+monitoring+cycle&amp;rft.pub=Council+of+Europe&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.coe.int%2Ft%2Fdg4%2Feducation%2Fminlang%2FReport%2FEvaluationReports%2FAustriaECRML3_en.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMinority+languages+of+Austria\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<div role=\"navigation\" class=\"navbox\" aria-labelledby=\"23x15px&amp;#124;border_&amp;#124;alt=&amp;#124;link=_Languages_of_Austria\" style=\"padding:3px\"><table class=\"nowraplinks collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner\" style=\"border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit\"><tbody><tr><th scope=\"col\" class=\"navbox-title\" colspan=\"2\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Languages_of_Austria\" title=\"Template:Languages of Austria\"><abbr title=\"View this template\" 